6590/f7fd9b8c2a) to learn more about Collective Health.\n\n__Care Navigation__\nCollective Health also offers a Care Navigation program where their team of Social Workers and Pharmacists review your care plan, help with care coordination and provide resources and support. Members who typically need the support of Care Navigation are those managing conditions such as cancer, autism spectrum disorder, gender affirmation surgery, transplant surgery and more. If you think you or your dependent would benefit from Care Navigation support, please reach out to the Collective Health Member Advocate team at 1-844-516-3832 from 4 AM - 6 PM PST Monday to Friday and 7 AM to 11 AM PST on Saturday or message them via the app or [Member Portal](https://my.collectivehealth.com/login?redirectTo=Landing\u0026loginEmail=). "}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4GpTqEeWFXpeJRrowCmYOo","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:53.521Z","updatedAt":"2020-01-01T18:09:33.893Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - Ext US Group - Dental","title":"Dental","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"25htp0Zh5c8BXBa9NPrca2","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:02.007Z","updatedAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:02.007Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - Dental - How It Works - US","sectionTitle":"How It Works","sectionDescription":"The Collective Health + Delta Dental Plan pays 100% of your preventive \u0026 diagnostic care such as exams, x-rays and fluoride applications, and a percentage of other services including fillings, crowns, implants and orthodontics for children and adults.\n1. The plan covers Diagnostic and Preventative care 100%.\n2. You pay the full cost of all other care until you meet the annual deductible. The deductibles are waived for Diagnostic and Preventative care and Orthodontics. \n3. Then the plan shares the cost with you.\n\nThe most the plan will pay for covered services per year is $2,000 per person. Diagnostic and Preventative (D\u0026P) and Orthodontics do not count toward the annual maximum of $2,000/per person.\n\nIf you use in-network providers, your costs will be lower because you pay a portion of the dentist's negotiated fees. This is the amount participating dentists have agreed to accept as payment in full.\n\nIf you use an out-of-network dentist, Collective Health + Delta Dental reimbursement is based on in-network contracted fees for Delta Dental PPO dentists. If your provider charges more than that, you're responsible for any amount exceeding the maximum reimbursable amount.\n\nTo see how much you'll pay for a service out of pocket, get a free predetermination. Your dentist can submit a predetermination to Delta Dental so you can make sure the plan covers a recommended procedure.\n\n*[deductible]: The amount you pay each year before the plan shares the cost of your health services.\n*[in-network]: In-network providers and facilities charge agreed-upon, lower, pre-negotiated fees.\n*[out-of-network]: Out-of-network providers can charge any amount for services, resulting in higher out-of-pocket costs. Maximum Reimbursable Charge limits apply.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"47ZKIXof4XCbosSZki2FK5","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:05.276Z","updatedAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:05.276Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - Dental - US - Plan Deta