 a share of Netflix stock at a set price at a later date. The purpose of the SOP is to allow you to accumulate options, and then exercise them later, when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. \n\nThere are two components of the SOP. \n\n1. __Free options.__ If you’re a __salaried employee__, we automatically allocate an amount equal to 5% of your annual salary to the SOP at no cost to you. During your first year at Netflix, this allocation is prorated from your hire date. \n2. __Supplemental Allocation.__ If you’re a __salaried or hourly employee__, you can direct as much of your salary or wages as you would like to the Annual Supplemental Stock Option Allocation (Supplemental Allocation) in exchange for stock options, subject to certain exceptions such as minimum wage requirements."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"nAKCdbZhkWaCgUUWe02S0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T01:29:50.594Z","updatedAt":"2018-09-21T17:34:26.291Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":20,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Calculating Your Options","sectionTitle":"Calculating Your Options","sectionDescription":"To figure out the number of options granted/purchased in any month, we apply the formula below.\n\n![SOP Math](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/3BcegQ12DuA2MIQwGK88oc/4a0437fb62624aabc57657ef75f31a78/SOP_Math.png)\n\n#### Example\n##### Assumptions:\n- Annual salary: $100,000\n- Free options granted: 5% = $5,000 annually ($416.67 monthly)\n- Supplemental Allocation elected: 12% = $12,000 annually ($1,000 monthly)\n- Netflix Closing Price: $200\n\n##### Monthly Calculation:\n![SOP Math Monthly Calc](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7LznyRvS1iSO4QsI0iwo0i/5f4923abb28ce6e7c90a90bfda980004/SOP_Math_Monthly_Calc.png)\n\n#### Note\nIf a partial option is calculated, it’s round