t/abx5xo923wy6/7LznyRvS1iSO4QsI0iwo0i/5f4923abb28ce6e7c90a90bfda980004/SOP_Math_Monthly_Calc.png)\n\n#### Note\nIf a partial option is calculated, it’s rounded down to the nearest whole option, and the remaining amount is carried over to the next month. __For employees outside the U.S.:__ The monthly free and Supplemental Allocation is converted to USD."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1EwfwhA3QQgI62Ugu8qKUA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T02:27:16.392Z","updatedAt":"2018-09-18T22:34:44.998Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":12,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Free Options","sectionTitle":"Free Options","sectionDescription":"Your free options become profitable when the current market price of Netflix stock is higher than the closing price at which it was granted to you. The closing price at which the options are granted to you is known as the Exercise or “Strike” Price.\n\nLet’s continue with the example above in which you were granted 5 free options at a $200 exercise price. Your options give you the right to purchase up to 5 shares at $200 each, no matter the current share price. So your options become profitable when the current price of Netflix stock is more than $200.\n\nHere’s an easy formula to see how much you earn.\n\n![SOP Free Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/27a5P1XgXOAK8aWMG2COSI/18c229af2affb4354bb0f2e5e7ba92aa/SOP_Free_Options.png)\n\nFor example, let’s assume you exercise all your free options when the market price of a Netflix share is $300. You purchase your 5 options at only $200 each, for a total cost of $1,000. \n\n![SOP Free Options Example](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/46C9rxb97aSQ8mq0G0KYYa/3e346d8d5a4309dca4bd8fb94c6393ca/SOP_Free_Options_Example.png)"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo