an the closing price at which it was granted to you. The closing price at which the options are granted to you is known as the Exercise or “Strike” Price.\n\nLet’s continue with the example above in which you were granted 5 free options at a $200 exercise price. Your options give you the right to purchase up to 5 shares at $200 each, no matter the current share price. So your options become profitable when the current price of Netflix stock is more than $200.\n\nHere’s an easy formula to see how much you earn.\n\n![SOP Free Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/27a5P1XgXOAK8aWMG2COSI/18c229af2affb4354bb0f2e5e7ba92aa/SOP_Free_Options.png)\n\nFor example, let’s assume you exercise all your free options when the market price of a Netflix share is $300. You purchase your 5 options at only $200 each, for a total cost of $1,000. \n\n![SOP Free Options Example](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/46C9rxb97aSQ8mq0G0KYYa/3e346d8d5a4309dca4bd8fb94c6393ca/SOP_Free_Options_Example.png)"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"47yg80VHWogieiGiiIgwqE","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T02:36:05.562Z","updatedAt":"2019-12-10T01:25:16.074Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":13,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Supplemental Allocation","sectionTitle":"Supplemental Allocation","sectionDescription":"For a Supplemental Allocation option, you must also allow for the cost of the options, which is 40% of the exercise price. That means if the price of stock is $200 when you purchase the options, you’ll exchange $80 of salary per option.\n\nWhen you’re ready to purchase shares with your options, you can purchase shares at the exercise price of $200 each, no matter the current market price. You’ve exchanged $80 of salary for each option. Now you have to pay $200 to buy the share, so your total cost is $280 per share. As you can see, you won’t recover the salary exchanged until our stock’s market price exceeds $280, which means the stock value must appreciate by at least 40%.\n\nHere’s a formula to see how much you can earn.\n\n![SOP - Supplemental Allocation](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/2UhjBvxnS0KssQ8qiSOICG/c1ab46bd49f084979acc8482fa389d58/SOP_-_Supplemental_Allocation.png)\n\nFor example, let’s assume you exercise all your Supplemental Allocation options when the market price of a Netflix share is $300. You paid $80 per share for your 12 options, and now you have to pay the exercise price of $200 each.\n\n![SOP - Supplemental Allocation Example](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/70eHdIU6YwY26IWgsoegc6/ea84ebec36150dbdda88964fcf78787a/SOP_-_Supplemental_Allocation_Example.png)\n\n#### Benefits of a Supplemental Allocation\n\n- __It reduces your taxable income.__ The salary you direct to the Supplemental Allocation isn’t taxed. You will be taxed when you exercise your stock options, and on the difference between the exercise price and the market value of the stock at the time of exercise.\n- __You can take your options with you if you leave Netflix.__ They generally expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of whether you’re a Netflix employee at that time."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1LWGggH5QcYqoma8aEMEwa","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-21T18:07:02.094Z","updatedAt":"2018-09-27T03:46:37.484Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"US SOP - Supplemental Allocation Considerations","sectionDescription":"#### Important Considerations for the Supplemental Allocation\nIt’s important you’re aware of things that may be affected by your participation in the Supplemental Allocation.\n\n- Because you reduce your cash compensation in exchange for receiving additional options, benefits that are normally determined and deducted from your pay can be impacted. For example, if you participate in the Netflix 401(k) Plan and contribute a percentage, your deferral is based on your bi-weekly pay. If you reduce your cash compensation by directing money to the Supplemental Allocation, you will also reduce your 401(k) deferral.\n- Be aware of the impact on your take-home pay — particularly if the health plans you’re enrolled in exceed the Health Benefit Allowance — so you don’t reduce your monthly pay to the point you can’t cover your premiums.\n- If you’re contributing a supplemental amount, your Short-Term Disability (STD) benefit is calculated based on your adjusted salary."}]}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"46w9gjDywoEgiWaQm48yM6","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-24T22:34:26.667Z","updatedAt":"2020-06-16T23:57:34.541Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":30,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"externalTab"}},"locale":"en-US"},"title":"Life Happens","locationBasedContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7ciucSHsGIIeC8smCAuUa4","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-29T19:43:10.448Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-18T17:01:48.572Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext US - Life Happens","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"71tweP9sK440IwCGyUagK0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-07-30T16:29:50.993Z","updatedAt":"2018-12-11T18:45:08.775Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentTy